Three corrections: operators go inside `pipe(...)` now; `.do(...)` is `tap(...)` in v7; `any` replaced with `string` since `input$` is typed `Observable<string>`.

Fix this snippet — it's using `mergeMap` for a search box, which races on fast typing:

```ts
import { debounceTime, distinctUntilChanged, mergeMap } from 'rxjs/operators';
declare const query$: Observable<string>;
declare function fetchBooks(q: string): Observable<Book[]>;

query$.pipe(
  debounceTime(300),
  distinctUntilChanged(),
  mergeMap(q => fetchBooks(q))
);
```

```ts
import { Observable } from 'rxjs';
import { debounceTime, distinctUntilChanged, switchMap } from 'rxjs/operators';

interface Book {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  author: string;
}

declare const query$: Observable<string>;
declare function fetchBooks(q: string): Observable<Book[]>;

export const bookSearch$: Observable<Book[]> = query$.pipe(
  debounceTime(300),
  distinctUntilChanged(),
  switchMap((q: string) => fetchBooks(q))
);
```

Swap `mergeMap` -> `switchMap`. `mergeMap` keeps every in-flight inner subscription alive — if the 1st request resolves AFTER the 3rd, the stale results get emitted last and overwrite your UI. `switchMap` cancels older inner observables the moment a newer outer value arrives.

```ts
import { Observable } from 'rxjs';
import { debounceTime, distinctUntilChanged, switchMap } from 'rxjs/operators';

interface Hit {
  id: string;
  label: string;
}

declare const searchBox$: Observable<string>;
declare function api(q: string): Observable<Hit[]>;

export const hits$: Observable<Hit[]> = searchBox$.pipe(
  debounceTime(200),
  distinctUntilChanged(),
  switchMap((q: string) => api(q))
);
```

Collapse the three `.pipe(...)` calls into one — `pipe` takes a variadic list of operators. And type `q` explicitly as `string` instead of `any`.

Add a minimum-length guard (>= 2 chars) and a trim step to this v7 typeahead:

```ts
import { Observable } from 'rxjs';
import { debounceTime, distinctUntilChanged, switchMap } from 'rxjs/operators';

declare function search$(q: string): Observable<string[]>;

export const out$ = (in$: Observable<string>) =>
  in$.pipe(
    debounceTime(300),
    distinctUntilChanged(),
    switchMap(q => search$(q))
  );
```

```ts
import { Observable } from 'rxjs';
import { debounceTime, distinctUntilChanged, filter, map, switchMap } from 'rxjs/operators';

declare function search$(q: string): Observable<string[]>;

export const out$ = (in$: Observable<string>): Observable<string[]> =>
  in$.pipe(
    debounceTime(300),
    map((q: string) => q.trim()),
    distinctUntilChanged(),
    filter((q: string) => q.length >= 2),
    switchMap((q: string) => search$(q))
  );
```

Order matters: trim BEFORE `distinctUntilChanged` so `"foo "` and `"foo"` dedupe, and filter AFTER distinct so we don't burn deduping slots on too-short strings. `switchMap` keeps its cancel-in-flight semantics.

Add a loading-state emission (before the network hop) to this typeahead stream:

```ts
