Refactor this v7 pipeline to use a single consolidated `pipe(...)` call and name the declared-function locals consistently (variables ending in `$`, functions prefixed with `search`):

```ts
import { Observable } from 'rxjs';
import { debounceTime, distinctUntilChanged, switchMap } from 'rxjs/operators';

declare function go(q: string): Observable<string[]>;
const stream = (src: Observable<string>) => {
  const a = src.pipe(debounceTime(300));
  const b = a.pipe(distinctUntilChanged());
  const c = b.pipe(switchMap(q => go(q)));
  return c;
};
```

```ts
import { Observable } from 'rxjs';
import { debounceTime, distinctUntilChanged, switchMap } from 'rxjs/operators';

declare function searchApi$(q: string): Observable<string[]>;

export const typeahead$ = (
  input$: Observable<string>
): Observable<string[]> =>
  input$.pipe(
    debounceTime(300),
    distinctUntilChanged(),
    switchMap((q: string) => searchApi$(q))
  );
```

Collapsing into one `pipe` avoids intermediate named bindings that don't pull their weight, and the `$` suffix on observable variables + `search` prefix on factory functions keeps names predictable.

Refactor this typeahead to extract a reusable `debouncedDistinct` custom operator; strict types, no `any`:

```ts
import { Observable } from 'rxjs';
import { debounceTime, distinctUntilChanged, switchMap } from 'rxjs/operators';

declare function api$(q: string): Observable<string[]>;

export const go = (in$: Observable<string>) =>
  in$.pipe(
    debounceTime(300),
    distinctUntilChanged(),
    switchMap(q => api$(q))
  );
```

```ts
import { Observable, OperatorFunction, pipe } from 'rxjs';
import { debounceTime, distinctUntilChanged, switchMap } from 'rxjs/operators';

declare function api$(q: string): Observable<string[]>;

const debouncedDistinct = (ms: number): OperatorFunction<string, string> =>
  pipe(debounceTime(ms), distinctUntilChanged());

export const go = (
  in$: Observable<string>
): Observable<string[]> =>
  in$.pipe(
    debouncedDistinct(300),
    switchMap((q: string) => api$(q))
  );
```

The standalone `pipe` from `'rxjs'` composes operators into a new `OperatorFunction<T, R>`; the observable's method `.pipe(...)` then consumes it like any built-in operator.

Refactor this v7 autocomplete to use an object-form `tap({ next, error })` side effect for logging before the switchMap:

```ts
