`mergeMap` here is the canonical bug — parallel requests can resolve out of order and the UI ends up showing results for a stale query.

You have two reasonable options: (1) emit an empty result array on empty input without hitting the network, or (2) `filter` out the empty values so the inner observable only runs on real queries. Option 2 is usually what you want — empty queries frequently match "reset the list" which is a separate concern. Put the `filter` AFTER `distinctUntilChanged` so you still benefit from de-duping when the user types "x" then backspaces back to "" then types "x" again.

